      "content": "```python\nimport sys\nsys.setrecursionlimit(2000000)\nparent = [0] * 1000001\nrank = [0] * 1000001\ndef find(i):\n    while parent[i] != i:\n        parent[i] = parent[parent[i]]\n        i = parent[i]\n    return i\ndef union(i, j):\n    root_i = find(i)\n    root_j = find(j)\n    if root_i != root_j:\n        if rank[root_i] < rank[root_j]:\n            parent[root_i] = root_j\n        elif rank[root_i] > rank[root_j]:\n            parent[root_j] = root_i\n        else:\n            parent[root_j] = root_i\n            rank[root_i] += 1\n```\nI'll read the input line-by-line to avoid loading the entire file into memory, and only store the `parent` and `rank` arrays which take exactly 8MB total for integers.\nSince I'm not storing the edge list, I process each pair `(u, v)` immediately upon reading, performing the union operation",
